headline: Stocks to Watch Recap: Electronic Arts, Lockheed Martin, Carnival, Alibaba
summary: ↗️ Electronic Arts (EA): The videogame maker is going private for $52.5 billion in what it billed as the largest-ever private-equity backed buyout. headline: Carnival Lifts Outlook Again As Booking Momentum Outpaces Capacity Growth
summary: Carnival Corporation & plc (NYSE: CCL) (NYSE: CUK) reported record third-quarter 2025 results, posting net income of $1.9 billion, or $1.33 per diluted share, up from $1.7 billion a year earlier. Adjusted net income was $2.0 billion, or $1.43 per diluted share, topping analyst expectations of $1.32. Revenue rose to $8.153 billion, beating the $8.101 billion consensus estimate and increasing from $7.9 billion last year. Adjusted EBITDA reached $3.0 billion.
